content.description: Incredible climbing through quality pockets, most of the route is perfectly flowing 5.10- up to a no hands rest where you can turn around and enjoy the view. The crux comes at the last two bolts where the wall steepens and the moves get pretty technical. The upper bolts seem to be in good shape and the falls through the crux would be clean.
content.protection: ~9 bolts. Bring some extendable draws for the lower parts.

content.description: Right of the Seductive Mermaid is a very inviting wide crack that just calls to be climbed. Those lured in by the Siren's Serenade will find a lovely top rope, or a wild lead that could leave you wrecked.
content.protection: variety of small cams, medium nut, and a #2 and #3 cam. Anchor using long chord from the Grog Supply anchor.

content.description: The 1st route at Footsteps, a long scooped trough, very pocketed, on the side, up to a series of amazing holds and bulge, and then goes right to traverse where you see Chris finishing up.

climbs.name: Seagulls Symphony, AKA The Incessant Weltering Splash

content.description: Pocketed arÃªte on left; blunt and well-featured with bigger huecos.
content.protection: Old bolts, and I think there's a short crack section, and perhaps I got some Tri-cams in; beware of singing seagulls and their nest-defending territorial swoops, as well as their nests coated with layers of white waste.
content.location: Where the edge of the cliff changes its aspect to face northwesterly.

content.description: Fun top rope, or RB lead. The two bolt anchor is accessible from the ledge that runs towards the anchors of the main South Face climbs, and is very solid. Grog Supply traverses right and shares this anchor.
content.location: On the separate wall to the right of the main pocketed wall.

content.description: Just classic fun pocket/jug pulling with a fun little overhanging start. You can pre-clip the first bolt by stemming off the boulder behind you. The bolts are completely rusted out, but fine if you don't fall! The anchor bolts are plenty fine.
content.protection: six bolts, and walk off bolted anchor out right.
content.location: Hike over the notch between the North and South Steps. Walk right to the top of the cliff to set the TR or walk straight down to the base.

climbs.name: Cutlass Supreme
climbs.fa: Tim Wilhelmi, Matthias Holladay & Richard Ludwig

content.description: More pockets, smaller though, and edges, over harder roof at top.
